f the interaction stage, Doppler\nboosting in the postshock flow is relevant even for mildly relativistic jets.\nFor clump-to-average wind density contrasts $\\gtrsim 10$, clump-jet\ninteractions could be bright enough to match the observed GeV luminosity in\nCyg~X-1 and Cyg~X-3 when a jet is present in these sources, with required\nnon-thermal-to-total available power fractions $\\sim 0.01$ and $0.1$,\nrespectively.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 18 Jan 2017 12:15:02 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-08-09"}
